    <h5 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Warning System</h5>
    <p class="font-normal text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-400">We have a warning system in place for users that fail to abide by rules and for people that fail to complete minimums on a day-to-day basis. We ensure that members complete their tasks as it improves the morale and the activity within TideRadio.UK. We hope users take the warning system not as an insult, but as a place to improve upon. All users start with 0 warnings, however, this could change based on the rules broken or minimums failed to complete. If you receive a warning, it will be placed down In a document.#
    <br/><br/>
    Below are the actions that take place upon being given a warning:
    <br/>
    <b>1 warning</b> = Message sent by manager outlining your issues with your work or behavior, with recommendations on how to improve and fix these issues.
    <br/>
    <b>2 warnings</b> = May result in a demotion or you’ll be stripped from your role, the Management team will look into what you have done and will tell you how you have to improve or be dismissed forever.
    <br/>
    <b>3 warnings</b> = Dismissal as you have failed to either improve or change your ways, you were already given chances to reform.
    <br/>
    Some rules have higher consequences and involve the use of the warning system. If suspended, you will temporarily see your staff title and permissions while the situation will be investigated by Management. It is left to the senior staff to decide how severely you are punished.
